track_notes:
A more gradual route up to the summit. Underfoot conditions are lots of grass with rocks hidden underneath.

A permit is required to activate this summit. Feel free to contact ZS6FY of ZS5AYC for assistance in obtaining the permit.

Summit is located next to a main forestry road and a high clearance 2x4 vehicle will be able to reach the trailhead.

A more direct route to the summit. The start is more steep than route 1. Part of this route goes through a patch of Bracken fern and fynbos.

A permit is required for access to the summit. Feel free to contact ZS6FY or ZS5AYC for assistance in obtaining a permit.

The trailhead is located next to a main forestry route and a high clearance 2x4 vehicle will be able to reach the trailhead.

This is a dirt track. It is a main forestry road and should be navigable with a high clearance 2x4 vehicle. Care should be taken during wet or dusty conditions.

A permit is required to use this track and for access to the summit. Feel free to contact ZS6FY or ZS5AYC for assistance in obtaining the correct permits.

This is a route to drive to ZS/MP-087. It is a dirt track and a main forestry route. A high clearance 2x4 vehicle will be able to travel on this route but care should be taken.

A permit is required to use this route. Feel free to contact ZS6FY or ZS5AYC for assistance in obtaining the correct permits.
